# Override .gitignore for npm publish. The `files` field in package.json is the
# authoritative allowlist for what ends up in the published tarball; this file
# simply prevents npm from inheriting .gitignore exclusions like `dist/` and
# `src/client/dist/` which we actually WANT to publish.
#
# Keep this minimal. Add entries only for files that match `files` patterns but
# should still be excluded from the tarball (e.g., test fixtures, source maps).

# Source maps are only useful during local debugging, skip them in the tarball
*.map
